Write Verilog code that uses different tasks to perform arithmetic operations.
ANSWER : 
ADD
    task add; 
        input a, b; 
        output s;
            initial begin s = a + b; 
end 
endtask

SUB
              task sub; 
              input a, b; output s; 
                    initial begin s = a - b; 
end 
endtask

MUL
          task mul; 
          input a, b; output s;
                      initial begin s = a * b;   
end 
endtask

DIV

task div; 
input a, b; output s;
initial begin s = (b != 0) ? a / b : 0;
end
endtask
